Rating: 4
After purchasing some excellent gingerbread from Whole Foods a couple of weeks ago, I've been looking for a recipe to make at home. This one was perfect! Of course, I made a few minor changes. I only had black strap molasses on hand, and I prefer dark gingerbread, so used that. I doubled the recipe, so used 3/4 c molasses & 1/4 c honey to balance it out a bit. I used orange zest instead of lemon, because I prefer the taste, and added fresh grated ginger as recommended by MN in 10/14/10 review. It was fantastic, and agree it only needed 30 min.

Rating: 4
This is my go-to gingerbread cake - and I love gingerbread cake. It always gets rave reviews. I usually go heavy on the spices, but not quite double, add more crystallized ginger, plus a good knob of fresh ginger, grated in. Also a twist or two of black pepper also makes a difference. I've never made the topping - fresh whipped cream does it for me.

Rating: 4
I made this for Mother's Day, my Mom loves Ginger Snap cookies and thought it would be a nice cake. She loved it. I put finely diced fresh ginger instead of crystalized (didn't have any left). I also did not have mascarpone cheese and did not want to go across town to get it and used cream cheese instead it was great, a bit thicker but really a good flavor, I added an extra tablespoon of honey. This cake was easy to make (even my four year old helped with out any problems, he cooks with us a lot). And, the cake is nice and light with a great flavor. Will make again any day or time of year.

Rating: 4
This was lovely! The gingerbread was the perfect holiday flavor I was seeking and the marscarpone cream was so good, too. I had never worked with marscarpone before, but I see more of it in my future.

Rating: 3
Delicious gingerbread! I used "heaping" spoonfulls for the spices, but did not double them. I baked mine in an 9" diameter cake pan & it came out perfectly after 30 minutes. It is not the most dense, moist, gingery cake I have ever had, but I prefer it this way. I thought this cake was the perfect level of moisture & flavor without being too heavy & overwhelming. Friends & family agreed. They LOVED it! I did not make the topping because I was planning to serve with warm caramelized pears & vanilla ice cream, but the cake was so good we just ate it plain. Can't wait to see how good it is the day after! So fast & easy, I will be making this all autumn & winter!

