This is a fantastic recipe. I increased ther ginger, cinnamon by 1/2 tsp. The crystallized ginger really sets it apart from the rest. I've made it twice, and both times have had a problem with the center sinking. I increased the cooking time by 5 minutes, and still had the same problem. Any ideas/suggestions? Also, I made the Apricot Sticky Sauce from another gingerbread recipe on Epicurious. I'd give that a big 4 forks! Yum!

Rating: 3
I've made this recipe a few times and agree that it is a good, quick, easy gingerbread recipe to have on hand. I've never made the mascarpone accompaniment, because I usually eat it plain or serve it with whipped cream. I also prefer a spicier gingerbread, so I up the spices to 1 generous tbs ginger, 1 tsp cinnamon, 1/2 tsp cloves and I add a few good grinds of black and white pepper as well. I've also found it comes out just as good with regular granulated sugar if you don't have brown sugar on hand. Happy baking!

