Rating: 3
I made this for Thanksgiving, along with the cover recipe in the Bon Appetit, November 2001 issue. It's a tradition and it didn't let us down. This gingerbread is a little stout in flavor, the kids liked the frosting better than they did the cake, but the adults loved it. The crystallized ginger was wonderful and made the cake moist and sweet. I did as the magazine suggested and started my TD dinner far in advance. I mixed the dry ingredients for this cake the night before and just whipped it up as soon as I pulled the turkey out of the oven, while it was carved, the cake cooked and filled the house with the warm, sweet smell of gingerbread. GREAT!